s awareness. With experience fighting wizards you will actually learn to appreciate the ones obsessed with getting their biggest nuke off. They are the easiest targets.<br><br>The most difficult wizard to fight is one with a good understanding of Yonder as a tool and that keeps lower level fast nukes memorized. With time you will learn to fear the fast low 50s draughts much more then the comet.<br><br>Whenever you are in range of 51+ spells in pvp I would suggest trying to raise your FR/CR each above 100. This is of course secondary to a MR well above 100, as you cannot even finish a well played caster if you have a poor MR.<br><br>Emperor Forestal of the Combine<br>Dark Knight of Vallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/28/01 4:03:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=222.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Comet</span><hr size=1> Update:<br>So far my experiences with ice comet have been decent.<br>Since i wear a guardian robe - wizards expect to kill me in one pop.. and arent even ready to dish out a second.  By the time they realize i'm not dead.. i'm gone. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A> at: 5/29/01 6:21:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/01 2:13:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreen